    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-26T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="1103"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1103">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760d.61/479: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-26T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >November 26, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 26—9:48 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>941. Today’s <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> published a front page editorial
                    devoted to a sarcastic and abusive personal attack upon Cajander, the Finland
                    Prime Minister whom it repeatedly characterizes as a clown. The editorial
                    stresses the point that the Finnish people are not in agreement with Cajander’s
                    rejection of the Soviet proposals, states that he belongs to the farsighted
                    school of Beck<note n="77" xml:id="d1103fn77">Józef Beck, Polish Minister for
                        Foreign Affairs until outbreak of war.</note> and Moscicki<note n="78"
                        xml:id="d1103fn78">Ignacy Moscicki, President of the Republic of Poland,
                        1926–1939.</note> and implies he is being led by England. It concludes by
                    expressing the hope that the Finnish people will not long permit marionettes
                    like Cajander to guide the Finnish Ship of State along the disastrous course of
                    Beck and Moscicki.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Helsinki.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
